      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "[205] Jesus accordingly does not deny that God rested on the seventh day after the six days of creation (against Ammon); but He affirms that since then He is ever active, even on the Sabbath-days, for man’s redemption. Nor does He speak of the law concerning the Sabbath as not of divine institution (Baur), as of no obligation, or as abrogated; but ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "He",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " as the ",
        "children": []
      },
